@* Shared 404 content. Rendered by the router's <NotFound> (a client-side nav to an unmatched route) and
   by Pages/NotFound.razor at /not-found (the server's UseStatusCodePagesWithReExecute target for route
   misses), so both paths show the same on-brand page instead of a bare "Page not found" line. Mirrors the
   original MVC NotFound view: distinct headline + a browse-anime CTA. *@

<PageTitle>Page not found · AniSync</PageTitle>

<section class="not-found-page">
    <p class="not-found-code" aria-hidden="true">404</p>
    <h1 class="page-title">Page not found</h1>
    <p class="library-empty">We couldn't find that page — it may have moved, or the link might be broken.</p>
    <div class="not-found-actions">
        <a class="btn-primary-action btn-login" href="/">Back to dashboard</a>
        <a class="btn-secondary-action" href="/discover">Browse anime</a>
    </div>
</section>
